### This is a real, plain-text ".http" request file — the format the
### "REST Client" and "Thunder Client" VS Code extensions (and JetBrains'
### built-in HTTP Client) all read directly. Each block starting with ###
### is one separate request. With one of those extensions installed, a
### "Send Request" link appears right above each block — no separate app,
### no GUI to learn, just a file that lives in your project like any other.

### Get every todo
GET http://localhost:4012/todos

### Get one todo by id
GET http://localhost:4012/todos/2

### Create a new todo — the body below is real JSON, sent exactly as written
POST http://localhost:4012/todos
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "Try sending this request for real"
}

### A request for something that doesn't exist — proves the real 404
GET http://localhost:4012/todos/999
